transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, thank you for calling Viagra. How can I assist you?

Speaker 2: Okay, so I ordered online from you guys the new Viagra AGB or whatever it is.

Speaker 1: You guys just sent me regular old Viagra.

Speaker 2: Hell, I get that a hell of a lot cheaper than what you guys told this to me for.

Speaker 1: What is your full name and date of birth?

Speaker 2: Glenn Kreitzer, K-R-E-I-T-L-I-T-O-M-Z-Z-E-R-E-R, and date of birth, 10-30-1962.

Speaker 1: Okay, well it looks like your order shipped out already.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I'm sitting here looking at it. It's incorrect. That's why I'm calling you.

Speaker 1: What's wrong with it?

Speaker 2: It's not Viagra AGB. It's not the new one.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so I saw you ordered the AGB. You said you opened it already.

Speaker 2: So can you take a look at the pills? Do they have the number 100 engraved on them?

Speaker 1: What?

Speaker 2: If you open the container and take a look at one of the pills, does it have the number 100 engraved on it?

Speaker 1: No, it says A, B, 3, 4. It's junk.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, it looks like they sent you the, it's not junk. They just sent you the wrong one.

Speaker 1: They sent you the classic Viagra.

Speaker 2: So don't worry, Glenn. I'll notify the pharmacy so that they're able to reship your order at no additional cost, okay?

Speaker 1: So they will be reshipping your order and you should be receiving it within the next three to five business days, okay?

Speaker 2: Don't ever make another mistake again or I won't do business with you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, they should be able to correct it. I don't know why they sent you that.

Speaker 2: But okay, so I'll ask them to reship your order, okay, Glenn?

Speaker 1: I'm going to throw this shit in the trash. It's no use.

Speaker 2: Yeah, you can throw it away. You don't have to keep it.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's gone.

Speaker 2: Okay, no worries.

Speaker 1: Don't screw me again.

Speaker 2: No, you should be receiving the right one. Okay, have a nice day, Glenn. Bye.

Speaker 1: Yeah, you too.
